ILS</span> &mdash; next binary event H1 2027. Gate 2 (market cap &lt;$2B): &#10003; Pass. Gate 3 (halal): &#10003; Pass.</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0; padding: 6px 10px; background-color: #1e1b4b; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; color: #fbbf24;\"><strong>Conviction: 2/5 &rarr; WATCH only.</strong> Gate 1 fails (no near-term binary &#8804;45 days). The data drop is yesterday&rsquo;s news. If you want to play Monday momentum, use a very tight stop &#8212; this is a trader&rsquo;s trade, not an investment. Run <code>analyze FDMT</code> for entry/stop/TP levels.</p>\n                      </td>\n                    </tr>\n                  </table>\n\n                  <!-- Candidate 2: PHVS -->\n                  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border: 1px solid #312e81; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n                    <tr>\n                      <td style=\"padding: 12px 14px;\">\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 4px 0;\">\n                          <span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #e0e7ff;\">&#128300; PHVS &mdash; Pharvaris N.V.</span>\n                          <span style=\"margin-left: 8px; padding: 1px 7px; background-color: #1e1b4b; color: #a5b4fc; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700;\">BIOTECH / RARE DISEASE</span>\n                        </p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #c7d2fe;\"><strong>Catalyst:</strong> CHAPTER-3 Phase 3 trial (deucrictibant XR, prophylaxis for HAE attacks) &mdash; topline data expected <strong>Q3 2026</strong>. Background: RAPIDe-3 Phase 3 (on-demand treatment) was POSITIVE in Dec 2025. CHAPTER-3 is the larger addressable market (preventive dosing). FDA NDA review ongoing for on-demand indication.</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #c7d2fe;\"><strong>Market cap:</strong> ~$1.74&#8211;2.08B (borderline &#8804;$2B gate) | <strong>Short interest:</strong> ~1.15&#8211;1.95% float (low)</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #c7d2fe;\"><strong>Edge:</strong> Phase 3 precedent positive (RAPIDe-3), CHAPTER-3 should follow; HAE prophylaxis market ~$2B+; competitive vs Takeda lanadelumab (injection) and BioCryst berotralstat (pill &#8212; closest comp)</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #c7d2fe;\"><strong>Gate check:</strong> Gate 1 (confirmed date &#8804;45 days): <span style=\"color: #fca5a5;\">&#10005; FAILS</span> &mdash; &ldquo;Q3 2026&rdquo; = no exact confirmed date. Gate 2 (market cap): <span style=\"color: #fbbf24;\">&#9888; Borderline $1.74&#8211;2.08B</span>. Gate 3 (halal): &#10003; Pass.</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 12px; color: #86efac;\"><strong>Halal:</strong> &#10003; Clean &mdash; rare genetic disease treatment</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0; padding: 6px 10px; background-color: #1e1b4b; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; color: #fbbf24;\"><strong>Conviction: 3/5 &rarr; WATCH.</strong> No confirmed date prevents Gate 1 clearance. If PHVS announces a CHAPTER-3 data readout date &mdash; especially if &#8804;14 days out &mdash; it immediately becomes INVESTIGATE. Set a stock alert. Run <code>analyze PHVS</code> when date confirms.</p>\n                      </td>\n                    </tr>\n                  </table>\n\n                  <!-- Scan summary -->\n                  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border: 1px solid #312e81; border-radius: 6px; opacity: 0.7;\">\n                    <tr>\n                      <td style=\"padding: 12px 14px;\">\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: #9ca3af;\">&#128311; Scan Summary &mdash; No Third Play Cleared Gates</p>\n                        <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 12px; color: #9ca3af; line-height: 1.6;\">The 30-search scan surfaced active PDUFA dates for centanafadine (Jul 24, Otsuka = large pharma &gt;$2B, excluded), Moderna mRNA-1010 (Aug 5, large cap excluded), and Ultragenyx DTX401 (Aug 23, ~$2.5B cap excluded). No additional small-cap (&lt;$2B) catalyst with confirmed date &#8804;45 days cleared all three gates this cycle. Note: <strong>CAPR (already held) IS the top conviction catalyst play</strong> with AdCom Jul 29 confirmed &#8212; it just happens to already be in the portfolio. Cash is deployed where conviction is highest.</p>\n                      </td>\n                    </tr>\n                  </table>\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </table>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <!-- CASH DEPLOYMENT -->\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"padding: 16px 24px 0 24px;\">\n            <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; border-radius: 8px;\">\n              <tr>\n                <td style=\"padding: 14px 18px;\">\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: #166534; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">&#128181; Cash Deployment &mdash; $450.23 Available</p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #14532d;\">Deployable (after $2 round-trip reserve): <strong>$448.23</strong>. Max per catalyst play (30% of $756.15): <strong>$226.85</strong>.</p>\n\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #14532d;\"><strong>Option A &mdash; Pre-earnings large-cap (META or AMZN):</strong><br>Buy ~1 share META (~$600?) or ~3 shares AMZN (~$65?) as pre-earnings momentum trade. Event Jul 29&#8211;30. Bullish setup on ad revenue + AI capex confirmation. Position: ~$200 = 26% of portfolio. Risk: if result disappoints, large-cap typically &#8722;5&#8211;10% (manageable). Halal: &#10003; both (tech/cloud platform businesses).</p>\n\n                  <p style=\"margin: 8px 0 4px 0; font-size: 13px; color: #14532d;\"><strong>Option B &mdash; Hold all cash:</strong><br>CAPR AdCom Jul 29 is a binary event that resolves in 9 days. If positive, you harvest TP1 (+$233 net) and redeploy $560+ into the next setup. If negative, you take the loss &#8212; but the $450 cash cushion means you survive and fight again. No forced rotation needed.</p>\n\n                  <p style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 0; padding: 8px 10px; background-color: #d1fae5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; color: #065f46;\"><strong>Recommended: Option B &mdash; Hold cash.</strong> With the single most important event of your portfolio (CAPR AdCom Jul 29) just 9 days away, adding a new position now creates unnecessary complexity and margin of error. The cash is working as dry powder and psychological cushion. After CAPR resolves, you&rsquo;ll have a clear picture for the next move. <em>Your call.</em></p>\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </table>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <!-- RISK SCORES -->\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"padding: 14px 24px 0 24px;\">\n            <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fde68a; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; border-radius: 8px;\">\n              <tr>\n                <td style=\"padding: 12px 16px;\">\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 11px; color: #92400e; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; font-weight: 600;\">Risk Scores</p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 13px; color: #374151; font-family: monospace; line-height: 1.8;\">\n                    CAPR &nbsp;| 73/100 | EXTREME &nbsp;| Pre-revenue biotech, binary FDA event, 100% position concentration<br>\n                    CASH &nbsp;| 0/100 &nbsp;| SAFE &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;| $450.23 uninvested &#8212; optionality value pre-AdCom\n                  </p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 6px 0 0 0; font-size: 12px; color: #78350f;\">CAPR risk is <em>by design</em> &mdash; you sized a binary catalyst play. The risk is in the entry decision, not the holding. Stay the course unless briefing docs (Jul 25) show FDA skepticism.</p>\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </table>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <!-- WHAT TO DO THIS WEEK -->\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"padding: 14px 24px 0 24px;\">\n            <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; border-radius: 8px;\">\n              <tr>\n                <td style=\"padding: 14px 18px;\">\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 11px; color: #166534; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">This Week&rsquo;s Checklist</p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 6px 0 0 0; font-size: 14px; color: #14532d; line-height: 1.8;\">\n                    <strong>Mon Jul 21:</strong> Monitor CAPR open. Confirm GTC sell $33&#8211;35 is live in IBKR.<br>\n                    <strong>Mon Jul 21:</strong> Check if FDMT gapped up on the positive AMD data (Friday announcement). Decide if you want a small momentum trade.<br>\n                    <strong>Thu Jul 24:</strong> Centanafadine (ADHD) FDA decision &mdash; not actionable for you (large pharma), but watch for sector sentiment.<br>\n                    <strong>Fri Jul 25:</strong> &#127941; <strong>READ FDA BRIEFING DOCS FOR CAPR.</strong> This is the most important day before AdCom. If FDA is skeptical of LVEF data &rarr; consider cutting before July 29. If supportive &rarr; hold.<br>\n                    <strong>Wed Jul 29:</strong> &#127941; <strong>CAPR ADCOM.</strong> Have your GTC sell active. Sell the reaction same-day at $33&#8211;35 regardless of outcome. Do NOT hold to PDUFA Aug 22.\n                  </p>\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </table>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <!-- IBKR INTELLIGENCE NOTE -->\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"padding: 14px 24px 0 24px;\">\n            <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 12px; color: #9ca3af; padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f9fafb; border-radius: 6px;\">&#128202; <strong>IBKR Intelligence</strong> &mdash; not available in routine mode. Trigger daily check in chat for full broker analytics (1D/MTD/YTD TWR, sector allocation, CAPR investment themes).</p>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <!-- EDUCATION MODULE -->\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"padding: 20px 24px 24px 24px;\">\n            <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background-color: #f1f5f9; border-radius: 8px;\">\n              <tr>\n                <td style=\"padding: 20px 24px;\">\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 11px; color: #475569; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">&#128218; Today you learned (#29)</p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 0; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #0f172a;\">Hyperscaler Capex Part 2 &mdash; The Actual Dollar Flows</p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 13px; color: #1e293b; line-height: 1.7;\">\n                    MSFT spends ~$80B annually on data center capex. Of the equipment slice: ~50% goes to AI accelerators (NVDA), ~15% to networking (AVCO/ARSP), ~15% to memory (MU/Samsung/Hynix). Multiply by four hyperscalers and ~$120B of the $725B combined 2026 capex flows directly to NVDA. This is why META and AMZN earnings on Jul 29&#8211;30 matter more than any single NVDA report: when META raises capex from $125B to $140B, NVDA&rsquo;s forward revenue estimate moves up in real-time. You don&rsquo;t wait for NVDA&rsquo;s August print. The transmission is direct and fast. This week: when META and AMZN give capex guidance, that IS the NVDA trade thesis update. Watch for phrases like &ldquo;we are accelerating AI infrastructure investment&rdquo; &mdash; that&rsquo;s the trigger.\n                  </p>\n                  <p style=\"margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 12px; color: #475569; font-style: italic;\">\n                    Also today: <em>Capex unit economics</em> &mdash; the revenue a hyperscaler generates per dollar of capex. Declining = AI capex bubble warning sign. Rising = the spend is productive.\n                  </p>\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </table>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <!-- FOOTER -->\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"padding: 0 24px 24px 24px; border-top: 1px solid #f3f4f6;\">\n            <p style=\"margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 10px; color: #9ca3af; line-height: 1.5;\">\n              Research output, not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Halal status based on business-activity screen (core business permissible). Generated Sunday July 20, 2026 ~06:00 Kuwait time (UTC+3).<br>\n              <strong>Prices:</strong> Yahoo Finance JSON API returned HTTP 403 on all endpoints (query1, query2) and stooq.com also unavailable. CAPR price ~$19.12 estimated from search results (last confirmed close Jul 17: $19.44). <strong>Verify all prices in IBKR before acting.</strong> | portfolio.json last_updated: 2026-07-19T06:00:00+03:00.\n            </p>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n\n      </table>\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n"}